# Energy weapons — ported from Fortune13 / LoneStar (SS13)

ent-N14WeaponLaserRCW = Laser RCW
    .desc = A rapid-cycling laser weapon developed by the US military shortly before the Great War. Fires a continuous stream of laser pulses in fully automatic mode, drawing from a high-output power cell. RCW stands for "Recycling Continuous Wave."

ent-N14WeaponPulsePistol = Pulse Pistol
    .desc = A compact EMP-pulse sidearm developed from classified pre-war military research into directed energy. Fires a short-range electromagnetic pulse bolt that devastates electronics and power armour alike. Small, but extraordinarily dangerous.

ent-N14WeaponPulseCarbine = Pulse Carbine
    .desc = A mid-range pulse weapon firing focused electromagnetic pulse bolts. Highly effective against robots, powered armour, and anything that runs on electronics. Requires a high-capacity power cell.

ent-N14WeaponPulseRifle = YK42b Pulse Rifle
    .desc = The infamous rifle developed by West-Tek for the US military. Fires concentrated EMP bolts at range with exceptional accuracy, capable of disabling armoured targets outright. One of the most feared military weapons of the pre-War era — and just as dangerous two centuries later.

ent-N14WeaponTeslaCannon = Tesla Cannon
    .desc = An experimental pre-War weapon that fires a crackling ball of electrical energy capable of arcing across multiple targets. Requires an advanced power cell and two hands to operate. Particularly devastating against groups in metallic armour. Not subtle.
